  <Docs>
    <summary>Represents a HarfBuzz color value (<c>hb_color_t</c>) with BGRA byte ordering.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`HBColor` wraps the HarfBuzz `hb_color_t` type, a packed 32-bit unsigned integer with the
byte order `0xBBGGRRAA` (blue in the high byte, alpha in the low byte). This is different
from <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColor>, which uses ARGB order (`0xAARRGGBB`). Always use the named
channel properties (<xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Red>, <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Green>,
<xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Blue>, <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Alpha>) rather than
manipulating the raw <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Value> directly.

This is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
// Create a fully-opaque red color
var red = new HBColor(255, 0, 0, 255);

// Convert from SKColor
SKColor skRed = SKColors.Red;
HBColor hbRed = skRed.ToHBColor();

// Read individual channels
byte r = hbRed.Red;
byte g = hbRed.Green;
byte b = hbRed.Blue;
byte a = hbRed.Alpha;
```
]]></format></remarks>
